        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-08-07T14:49:01.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"163108\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>I\u2019ll bite, what do they say about the water table in Puligny?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Oh, just that it\u2019s very high (dig a cellar, get a swimming pool). These vines seem very vigorous, with lots of lateral shoots at the top of the canopy. Compare this to the videos from Vosne posted in the 2020 vintage thread and you\u2019ll notice the difference immediately.</p>",
